    <stitle>CAM AIR FOUNDATION BRAKES - BRAKE CHAMBER - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>The tamper resistant spring brake has been factory sealed for your protection. There are no user
                    serviceable parts inside the spring brake chamber. If you experience any damage or failure to the
                    spring brake chamber, replace the complete assem- bly. Never attempt to disassemble the spring brake
                    chamber as serious personal injury or death could result from accidental sudden release of the high
                    energy spring.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cage spring (PARKING) brake if equipped. Refer to GROUP 04 - BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master
                Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect air hoses/lines from chamber.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect chamber push rod clevis from slack adjuster.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fasteners securing the brake chamber to the mounting bracket. Remove chamber.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
